news.title: Pay property tax by July 31 to avail benefits: Ludhiana civic body chief
news.para: Ludhiana residents have one week left to pay pending property taxes without incurring interest or penalties under the one-time settlement (OTS) scheme. MC Commissioner Aaditya Dachalwal urges residents to take advantage of this opportunity by July 31. Zonal suvidha kendras will remain open this weekend to facilitate payments.

news.title: Odisha RERA notifies formation of CDR cell for resolving disputes
news.para: Odisha Real Estate Regulatory Authority (ORERA) has established a Conciliation and Dispute Resolution (CDR) cell to facilitate amicable resolutions between homebuyers and promoters, preventing protracted legal battles. Approved by the housing and urban development department, the cell comprises five members, including representatives from developers' and allottees' associations. Registered allottee associations are invited to nominate a member by July 30, 2025.

news.title: Government decides to regularise B-khata buildings in Bengaluru, leaves out vacant plots
news.para: The Karnataka government has decided to regularize existing B khata buildings and multi-story apartments in Bengaluru constructed on unauthorized layouts, provided they were registered before September 30, 2024. Vacant plots with B khata status are excluded from this regularization. Individual buyers of plots from unauthorized subdivisions may be eligible for a khata under specific conditions.

news.title: Thirteen illegal colonies built on 40 acres demolished in week-long drive in Gurugram
news.para: Gurugram's Department of Town and Country Planning (DTCP) conducted demolition drives across 13 unauthorized colonies, targeting illegal urban development. Supported by local police, the DTCP cleared over 40 acres of illegally carved-out colonies and razed more than 50 structures between July 18 and July 23.

news.title: Chettinad Cement, JK Lakshmi in race to acquire Deccan Cements
news.para: Deccan Cements, with an expected operational capacity of 4 million tonnes by the end of this year, is seeking an enterprise value of $360 million (Rs 3,110 crore) for the company, said the people aware of the discussions. That translates into about $90 for each tonne of capacity.

news.title: Chennai civic body clears two lakh tonnes of building waste in six months
news.para: Greater Chennai Corporation has removed 2 lakh tonnes of construction and demolition waste across all 15 city zones in the past six months. Supported by Premier Precision Surface, the initiative uses 168 vehicles to clear approximately 1,000 tonnes of waste daily, which is then recycled into paver blocks. New disposal guidelines are in effect, with fines issued to violators.

news.title: Bombay HC directs Maharashtra RERA to restore hybrid hearings within four weeks
news.para: Bombay High Court has instructed MahaRera to reinstate hybrid hearings within four weeks, allowing parties the option of physical or virtual appearances. The court emphasized that access to justice includes the right to appear physically. MahaRera has also been directed to review its procedures for urgent listing, order execution, and pronouncements.

news.title: Act against power, water to illegal buildings: Bombay HC tells Thane civic body
news.para: The Bombay High Court has directed the Thane municipal commissioner to investigate illegal constructions, focusing on power and water connections and holding responsible civic officers accountable. The court expressed distress over encroachments in Thane's green zones and emphasized the need for vigilance to prevent unauthorized constructions and protect the public from fraud.

news.title: Karnataka cabinet approves 1% fire cess on newly constructed multi-storeyed buildings
news.para: Karnataka cabinet also approved amendments to the Karnataka Global Capability Centre (GCC) Policy 2024-29 to improve clarity and consistency in the policy language and structure without altering its core provisions or objectives.

news.title: Average long-term US mortgage rate eases to 6.74%, keeping home loan borrowing costs elevated
news.para: Mortgage rates saw a slight dip this week, with the 30-year rate at 6.74% and the 15-year at 5.87%, yet they offer minimal relief amidst high home prices. The housing market continues to struggle with sales remaining sluggish since 2022. Economists anticipate rates to stay above 6% throughout the year, influenced by factors like inflation and Federal Reserve policies.

news.title: DLF-Trident’s ‘The Westpark’ nets ₹2,300 crore from phase-1 sellout
news.para: DLF, via DLF Home Developers, has entered Mumbai's residential market with The Westpark in Andheri West, partnering with Trident Realty. The project's phase-1, featuring 416 units across four 37-story towers, sold out within a week, generating over ₹2,300 crore in sales. This launch is part of a larger 10-acre plan that will include eight residential towers.

news.title: TDI Infrastructure repays ₹2,000 crore loans to become debt free
news.para: TDI Infrastructure Ltd. has announced that it is now a debt-free company, having repaid its entire Rs 2,000 crore loan without any restructuring or waivers. The company is now focusing on asset consolidation and the development of townships and commercial properties.

news.title: Canada's City Office REIT to be taken private in near $1.1 billion deal
news.para: City Office REIT has agreed to be acquired by MCME Carell, an Elliott Investment affiliate, in a $1.1 billion all-cash deal, including debt assumption. MCME Carell will purchase outstanding shares for $7.00 each, a 26% premium.

news.title: Indian construction equipment sales dip 1% in Q1 FY26; exports surge 34%
news.para: India's construction equipment industry experienced a slight downturn at the beginning of FY26, with sales marginally decreasing by 1%. While domestic sales saw a dip, exports surged significantly, driven by overseas demand. Industry leaders emphasize the need to accelerate infrastructure project execution to revitalize demand in the coming quarters.

news.title: The Phoenix Mills' net profit rises 2.06% in Q1 FY26
news.para: Phoenix Mills reported a 2.06% increase in net consolidated profit, reaching ₹319.91 crore in Q1 FY26. Total income grew by 4.47% to ₹984.50 crore. The retail segment saw a 12% surge in consumption, while residential sales more than tripled, highlighting strong performance across key business areas. Rajesh Kulkarni's term as a whole-time director has been extended.

news.title: Phoenix Mills to acquire CPP Investments' 49% stake in ISMDPL for ₹5,449 crore
news.para: Phoenix Mills (PML) is set to acquire CPP Investments' 49% stake in Island Star Mall Developers (ISMDPL) for ₹5,449.16 crore, gaining full ownership. The transaction, unfolding over three years, will consolidate PML's control over key retail assets like Phoenix MarketCity Bengaluru and enhance shareholder value. ISMDPL's revenue has seen substantial growth, reaching ₹919.7 crore in FY25.

news.title: IndiQube Spaces IPO fully subscribed on day 2; retail portion subscribed over seven times
news.para: IndiQube Spaces' ₹700-crore IPO was fully subscribed on its second day, driven by strong retail and non-institutional investor interest. The IPO, closing on July 25, 2025, saw an overall subscription of 2.68 times, with significant oversubscription in the retail segment. The company previously raised ₹314 crore from anchor investors, including prominent mutual funds and institutions.

news.title: Concorde to jointly develop 2.16 acres residential project in East Bengaluru
news.para: Concorde has partnered to develop Concorde Élevé, a high-rise residential project on Old Madras Road in East Bengaluru. This project, spread across 2.16 acres, features a development potential of 3.2 lakh sq ft and a gross development value of ₹475 crore.

news.title: Sri Lotus Developers' IPO to open on July 30, price band set at ₹140-₹150 per equity share
news.para: Sri Lotus Developers and Realty is launching its IPO. The price is ₹140 to ₹150 per share. The IPO opens on July 30, 2025, and closes on August 1, 2025. The IPO is a fresh issue of shares. The company has completed several projects. Revenue and profit have increased. Monarch Networth Capital and Motilal Oswal are the lead managers.

news.title: ACC's net profit up 4.36% in Q1 FY26
news.para: ACC reported a 4.36% rise in consolidated net profit, reaching ₹375.42 crore in Q1 FY26, driven by strong cement demand and favorable macroeconomic conditions. The company's total income grew by 16.79% to ₹6,155.58 crore. ACC anticipates continued strong cement demand, projecting a 6-7% growth for FY26, fueled by housing and infrastructure investments.
